303
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:17,320
It's them…

304
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:20,740
This is all their fault.

305
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,800
I treated him so well.

306
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:27,380
Why did he betray me?

307
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:32,680
The one you're talking about is the person in the portrait,

308
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:35,260
your first husband.

309
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,740
It is him.

310
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,920
During my childhood,

311
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:55,100
my younger sister was kidnapped.

312
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:58,080
When we met,

313
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:04,280
she had become a courtesan who was skilled at pipa.

314
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:08,900
At that time, I was already married.

315
00:27:08,900 --> 00:27:14,080
But I never expected on the Mizar Festival…

316
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:18,840
On the Mizar Festival, I discovered

317
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:21,900
she was having an affair with my husband.

318
00:27:21,900 --> 00:27:23,760
The two people I loved the most.

319
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:25,920
The two people I trusted the most.

320
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:28,780
Both betrayed me.

321
00:27:28,780 --> 00:27:33,080
To save face, I gave her a cup of poisoned wine.

322
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:40,200
But unexpectedly, my husband drank the wine.

323
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,008
 No! 

324
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:46,920
After my husband passed away,

325
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,180
my younger sister also disappeared.

326
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:53,540
I really looked for her for a very long time.

327
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:58,920
In the end, I found her in a grave.

328
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:08,920
The two of them were still tightly embracing each other!

329
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:19,720
No.

330
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:23,240
It's not like that.

331
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,012
It's not like this.

332
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,400
It's not like that.

333
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,680
It's not like that.

334
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:33,700
That despicable woman wasn't my younger sister at all.

335
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:40,740
She was just a courtesan who seduced my husband.

336
00:28:40,740 --> 00:28:42,040
She deserved to die.

337
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:43,600
She did not choose to be a decent person,

338
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:45,880
instead, she seduced my husband.

339
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,520
She deserved to be torn to pieces.

340
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:49,480
She deserved to be skinned and deboned.

341
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:53,980
She deserved to be humiliated by the world and laughed at by everyone.

342
00:28:53,980 --> 00:28:59,020
So you killed those who resembled your younger sister?

343
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:06,512
 Does it look good? 

344
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,676
 Pretty. 

345
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,280
They deserved to die.

346
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:15,800
And those despicable men!

347
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:20,580
Why do they always love those courtesans?

348
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:25,660
In this world, not everyone has the right to choose their own life.

349
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:28,080
Among them, many were born in the music house

350
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:31,620
